Served as first course. Lots of compliments. Followed recipe closely and used the day ahead recommendations. I recommend that you dress the watercress at the last moment to avoid wilting. Goat cheese was divine and super simple to prepare.

Rating: 4
Best beet salad on the planet and our family-favorite holiday salad. We've tried probably a dozen beet salad recipes over the years but this one is far and away the best. It's super easy and can be made in advance so it is perfect for Thanksgiving or Christmas. Much better and easier than the molded beet and pistachio salad (also on this site). This one is a total winner!

Rating: 4
I don't even like beets and I thought this was delicious! (beets arrived in our veg delivery this week so had to use them somehow). I roasted some shallots along with the beets (adding them halfway thru the beet time) and toasted some pecans to put on top (ideas from other recipes) -- I would definitely do this again as they both added a lot to the final result. I also used fresh tarragon (don't care for the dried). Fantastic and different, husband raved too!

Rating: 3
I used an already-herbed goat cheese, and made a "crust" for the cheese of toasted hazlenuts and fresh tarragon. I also used fresh tarragon in the vin., and put a few extra nuts in too, that were leftover from the crust. All in all, it was very, very fresh and tasty and savory and beety. The vin. was fine--the true stars are the beets and the goat cheese, but I suppose they might be too center- stage without the greens, etc.

